# Coding Standards and Best Practices

## Code Quality
1. Strictly enforce Flutter and Dart lint rules via analysis_options.yaml
2. No dynamic types unless absolutely necessary
3. Ensure proper null safety implementation
4. Use final/const appropriately
5. Implement proper error handling

## String Management
1. No hardcoded strings allowed
2. Use localization files for all UI text
3. Support multi-language using Flutter localization
4. Extract constant values to dedicated constants files

## State Management
1. Use Riverpod for state management
2. Minimize widget rebuilds:
   - Use selective Consumer widgets
   - Implement proper ref.watch usage
   - Use selectors for granular state updates

## Model Handling
1. Use Freezed for immutable data models
2. Implement sealed classes for union types
3. Proper error handling in model parsing
4. Define explicit types - avoid var

## Testing
1. Follow Test-Driven Development (TDD) when possible
2. Required test coverage:
   - Unit tests for business logic
   - Widget tests for UI components
   - Integration tests for features
3. Use mocktail for mocking in tests

## Documentation
1. Document all public APIs
2. Include example usage in complex utilities
3. Maintain README files for each module
4. Use proper dartdoc comments
